<dl id="n05032g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05032g">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05032g"> 32(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> the Adversary <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n05032g"><li>FW 81.19 </li><li><a href="../../flex/d/lexd.htm#n05032g">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/d/l39d.htm#n05032g">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n05032g">MS BL 47472-262</ms> </li><li>JJA 46:094 <a name="dd5" href="../../FF/fdra/dda.htm#dd5">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/d/dd5.htm#n05032g">Draft: I.4&sect;1.5</a>/2.5</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">The devil, in human form, accosted him in a street one day and asked him where he was going. &lsquo;I go where God calls me,&rsquo; said Martin. &lsquo;Know then,&rsquo; said <mark>the Adversary</mark>, &lsquo;that go where you may, do what you will, I will constantly oppose you.&rsquo; <small> Margaret Maitland, <a name="MMLL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MMLL"><cite title="source">Life and Legends of St. Martin of Tours (316-397)</cite></a> (1908) 22</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
